---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - WattCostGuide" description="Privacy policy, cookies, analytics, and advertising disclosures for WattCostGuide.">
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide is designed to provide appliance electricity cost estimates with minimal personal data
      collection. This page explains analytics, cookies, and advertising disclosures.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide does not require an account to use the calculators. Calculator values such as watts,
      hours, and electricity rate are processed in your browser and are not submitted through a form.
    </p>
    <p>
      Like most websites, hosting and analytics services may collect basic technical information such as
      browser type, pages visited, approximate location, referring pages, and device information.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Cookies and advertising</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide may use cookies or similar technologies for analytics, site performance, and advertising.
      Cookies can help remember preferences, measure page performance, prevent abuse, and understand which
      pages are useful to readers.
    </p>
    <p>
      If advertising is displayed, third-party advertising partners, including Google, may use cookies or
      similar technologies to serve ads, limit repeated ads, measure ad performance, and personalize ads based
      on visits to this and other websites.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Google AdSense and third-party vendors</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide may participate in Google AdSense or other advertising programs. Google and its partners
      may use advertising cookies to show ads based on a user's prior visits to this site or other sites.
    </p>
    <p>
      Users can learn more about how Google uses information from sites and apps that use its services by
      visiting Google's published advertising and privacy resources. Users may also manage personalized ad
      settings through their Google account or browser settings.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide may use privacy-conscious analytics or hosting analytics to understand traffic patterns,
      device types, popular pages, and technical issues. Analytics data is used to improve the site and is not
      used to identify individual readers directly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can disable cookies in your browser settings, use private browsing mode, or use available ad settings
      tools from advertising providers. Disabling cookies may affect some website preferences, but the core
      electricity cost calculators should remain usable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide may link to external websites, including utility resources, manufacturer information, or
      privacy resources. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of external websites.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Policy updates</h2>
    <p>
      This policy may be updated as the site adds analytics, advertising, consent tools, or new features.
      The latest version will be posted on this page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, advertising questions, or correction requests, use the contact page.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
